        "title": "Add local Telegram channel SDK driver",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add SDK-level local channel driver types, transcript semantics, and capability metadata\n- expose `adapter: channel` for deterministic Telegram local upstream runs without live credentials or VM orchestration\n- add `multipass channel-matrix --json` plus example Telegram local fixtures for future OpenClaw QA Lab consumption\n\n## Scope notes\n- This is the openclaw/multipass messaging/channel SDK foundation, not Canonical Multipass VM runner work.\n- Model responses stay out of scope; the local provider only supports deterministic QA fixture replies (`ack`, `echo`, or `none`).\n- PR openclaw/openclaw#91487 was used only for shape ideas: per-channel selection, metadata, and matrix visibility.\n\n## Testing\n- `pnpm verify`\n- `pnpm dev channel-matrix --json`\n- `pnpm dev roundtrip telegram-local-dm --config fixtures/examples/multipass.example.yaml --json`",
